<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#40c1ff">Originally posted by Ryzak on 04-05-2001 11:50 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Greetings members of Altered Destiny.  My name is Ryzak Myrdhyn, leader of the Sages of Shadow.  Tillan was in our guild for about a month, during which time we got to know him.  I have been following this post for the last couple of days, and thought it was time for my thoughts on Tillan.  He is a very smart and resourceful individual; however, he lacks what is essential (in my opinion) to be a guild member.  He lacks the desire to help his fellow guildmates.  It was obvious from almost the beginning that he was looking out for #1.  He rarely chatted on guild channel, nor offered his help to fellow guildmates.  His concern was levelling and acquiring loot for himself.  He was fairly rude to other guild members, at which time, I asked him to be more polite and helpful towards guildmates. His response was "I don't do the PR thing."  My opinion of him dropped rather rapidly after that.  
Knowing a couple of members of Altered Destiny,and reading your guild rules, I can honestly say, that Tillan would probably not be a good choice for your guild.  His sense of "me first" is not what I think, any guild wants.  He also states here, that he wants to "prove his worth" to Altered Destiny, but he never even attempted to prove his worth to any other guild.  Although the Sages are small, we are a very tight-knit group, and one I am proud to lead.

Thank you for your time, and if you have any further questions, please give me a tell online.

And Cymrych, as Helcion would say.....bleah  :)</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
